name: app.R
content:
library(shiny)
library(readr)
library(dplyr)
library(DT)

# Load preprocessed RDS files
mass_comm_occupation_data <- readRDS("appdata/mass_comm_occupation_data.rds")
occupation_wages <- readRDS("appdata/occupation_wages.rds")
top_skills <- readRDS("appdata/top_skills.rds")
key_technologies <- readRDS("appdata/key_technologies.rds")

# Precompute choices
job_titles <- c("-", sort(unique(mass_comm_occupation_data$Title)))
states <- c("-", sort(unique(occupation_wages$AREA_TITLE)))

# Shiny UI
ui <- fluidPage(
  tags$head(
    tags$link(rel = "stylesheet", type = "text/css", href = "custom.css")
  ),
  titlePanel("Mass Communications Careers"),
  fluidRow(
    column(
      width = 4,
      selectInput("job_title", "Select a Job Title:", choices = job_titles, selected = "-"),
      selectInput("state", "Select a State:", choices = states, selected = "-"),
      h2("Job Details"),
      textOutput("description"),
      h3("Alternate Titles"),
      textOutput("alt_titles"),
      h3("Bureau of Statistics Data"),
      DT::dataTableOutput("stats_table")
    ),
    column(
      width = 4,
      h4("Top Skills"),
      DT::dataTableOutput("skills_table")
    ),
    column(
      width = 4,
      h4("Key Technology Skills"),
      DT::dataTableOutput("technology_table")
    )
  ),
  fluidRow(
    column(
      width = 12,
      tags$footer(
        "Data for this dashboard has come from the ",
        tags$a(href = "https://www.onetcenter.org/database.html", "O*NETÂ® 29.1 Database", target = "_blank"),
        " and the ",
        tags$a(href = "https://www.bls.gov/oes/tables.htm", "U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics Occupational Employment and Wage Statistics", target = "_blank"),
        "."
      )
    )
  )
)

# Shiny Server
server <- function(input, output) {
  selected_job <- reactive({
    req(input$job_title != "-")
    mass_comm_occupation_data %>%
      filter(Title == input$job_title)
  })
  
  filtered_wages <- reactive({
    req(input$job_title != "-", input$state != "-")
    occupation_wages %>%
      filter(OCC_CODE == selected_job()$OCC_CODE & AREA_TITLE == input$state)
  })
  
  output$description <- renderText({ selected_job()$Title })
  output$alt_titles <- renderText({ selected_job()$`Alternate Titles` })
  
  output$stats_table <- DT::renderDataTable({
    filtered_wages() %>%
      select(H_MEAN, A_MEAN, H_MEDIAN, A_MEDIAN) %>%
      rename(
        `Mean Hourly Wage ($)` = H_MEAN,
        `Mean Annual Wage ($)` = A_MEAN,
        `Median Hourly Wage ($)` = H_MEDIAN,
        `Median Annual Wage ($)` = A_MEDIAN
      )
  }, options = list(pageLength = 5, scrollX = TRUE))
  
  output$skills_table <- DT::renderDataTable({
    top_skills %>%
      filter(OCC_CODE == selected_job()$OCC_CODE) %>%
      select(`Element Name`, LV) %>%
      rename(Skill = `Element Name`, Level = LV)
  }, options = list(pageLength = 5, scrollX = TRUE))
  
  output$technology_table <- DT::renderDataTable({
    key_technologies %>%
      filter(OCC_CODE == selected_job()$OCC_CODE) %>%
      select(`Commodity Title`, Example) %>%
      rename(Technology = `Commodity Title`, Example = Example)
  }, options = list(pageLength = 5, scrollX = TRUE))
}

# Ensure shinyApp() is correctly placed at the end
shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server, options = list(launch.browser = TRUE))
